news.title: Nuvoco Vistas' net profit dips 50.09% in Q4 FY24
news.para: Nuvoco Vistas' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 2,940.61 crore in Q4 FY24, a minor growth of 0.33 per cent Rs 2,930.96 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Indiabulls Real Estate's subsidiary acquires Sky Forest Projects for Rs 646.71 crore
news.para: Sky Forest Projects (SFPPL) owns a residential project-Sky Forest, situated in Lowel Parel, Mumbai. The acquisition will help expand Indiabulls Real Estate’s presence in Mumbai.

news.title: China's Jinke Property Group prepares initial plans for court-led restructure debt
news.para: The company, based in southwestern Chongqing, is among many developers defaulting on debt since the sector slipped into crisis in mid-2021 but is the first to file its restructuring plan with a Chinese court.

news.title: China's Fantasia proposes $1.3 billion debt to equity swap for creditors
news.para: Cheering the restructuring agreement, shares of Fantasia jumped more than 11% on Tuesday morning, outperforming the 0.4% fall in the Hang Seng Mainland Properties Index.

news.title: Strained Chinese cities struggle to pay home buying subsidies
news.para: The 30-year-old now pays 6,000 yuan of her 8,000 monthly salary on the mortgage for the 1.1 million yuan apartment and another 1,800 yuan to rent another one, relying on her parents for other basic expenses.

news.title: Germany’s Vonovia reports net profit of $359 million in Q1 2024
news.para: Shares in early trade were up 2.3% in Vonovia, which also said it expects property values to bottom out this year, It posted a profit of 335.5 million euros ($359 million), bouncing back from a loss of 2.088 billion a year earlier.

news.title: China Vanke's first public commercial REIT falls in early trade on debut
news.para: The CICC-SCPG Consumption Infrastructure real estate investment trust (REIT) listed in Shenzhen is backed by shopping centres owned by SCPG Holdings, the commercial property platform of Vanke.

news.title: NFRA penalises three auditors in Reliance Home Finance case
news.para: ​A fine of Rs 1 crore has been levied on audit firm Dhiraj & Dheeraj, Rs 50 lakh on Piyush Patni and Rs 10 lakh on Pawan Kumar Gupta. Both Patni and Gupta are partners of the Mumbai-based audit firm Dhiraj & Dheeraj.

news.title: Can Fin Homes' net profit up 26.08% in Q4 FY24
news.para: Can Fin Homes's net total income stood at Rs 927.64 crore in Q4 FY24, a growth of 21.37 per cent from Rs 764.29 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: EFC (I) ventures into managing SM REIT
news.para: The board also approved establishment of EFC Estate, a wholly-owned subsidiary, for potential strategic partnership and investments in commercial real estate projects, IT Park projects.

news.title: DDA looks to finish Dwarka Golf View Apartments project by June end
news.para: After receiving enthusiastic response for Dwarka Golf View Apartments, the DDA is now working on a war footing to meet the deadline of finishing the project by June end," a statement said.

news.title: WeWork reaches settlement with creditors, rebuffs Adam Neumann bid
news.para: WeWork has struck an agreement with senior lenders, who have agreed to provide the business with roughly $450 million in Chapter 11 and exit financing in exchange for equity in the reorganized business.

news.title: Aurum PropTech posts net loss of Rs 4.65 crore in Q4 FY24
news.para: Aurum PropTech's consolidated net total income stood at Rs 65.74 crore in Q4 FY24, a growth of 28.07 per cent from Rs 51.33 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: China: Property developers' shares rally on stimulus hopes
news.para: Hong Kong's Hang Seng Mainland Properties Index jumped 4.3% in the morning session, while mainland China's CSI 300 Real Estate Index surged 6.9%, both to near four-month highs.

news.title: Hong Kong court adjourns liquidation hearing of Kaisa Group to May 27
news.para: Shenzhen-based Kaisa has been working on an offshore debt restructuring for two years after defaulting on its $12 billion of offshore debt in late 2021.

news.title: Abu Dhabi’s Aldar Properties reports 88% increase in net profit for Q1 2024
news.para: Net profit rose to 1.57 billion UAE dirhams ($427.5 million), beating analyst expectations of 1.03 billion dirhams, LSEG data showed, Revenue for the quarter totalled 5.6 billion dirhams, up 83% year on year.

news.title: China: CIFI Holdings gets bondholder approval on restructuring plan
news.para: Shanghai-based CIFI defaulted on payments tied to a convertible bond in October, 2022, and has been working with its creditors for repayment solutions since.
